<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:170696">skillet</a>, <a href="/user/uid:53959">Gary Norton</a>, <a href="/user/uid:105891">JML9999</a>, <a href="/user/uid:209053">Anthony Page aka SecondComing</a>, <a href="/user/uid:199851">TRPChicago</a>, <a href="/user/uid:96793">LamontCranston</a>, <a href="/user/uid:158085">commonmass</a>, <a href="/user/uid:204262">cherish0708</a>, <a href="/user/uid:332959">Icicle68</a>, <a href="/user/uid:236557">Pilotshark</a>, <a href="/user/uid:154504">jfromga</a>, <a href="/user/uid:113074">HappyinNM</a>, <a href="/user/uid:32406">Eyesbright</a>, <a href="/user/uid:96369">Matt Z</a>, <a href="/user/uid:143105">gdwtch52</a>, <a href="/user/uid:143843">bobatkinson</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75006">DSPS owl</a>, <a href="/user/uid:641606">Dodgerdog1</a>, <a href="/user/uid:193700">sethtriggs</a>, <a href="/user/uid:824659">Old Sailor</a>, <a href="/user/uid:5359">Liberal Thinking</a>, <a href="/user/uid:156548">Larsstephens</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Woke up to <i>Morning Ho</i> today, where Sekulow's propaganda piece was presented as if it were objective news. &nbsp;Klein was given a chance to opine, and he characterized the presentation as a mess.</p>
<p>He properly distinguished between the partisan targeting of Tea Party groups, which is wrong and dangerous as an IRS activity; the investigation of those groups once targeted, though, Klein rightly pointed out was IRS properly doing its job. &nbsp;Referral of these groups initiated investigation of them, which was apparently done at other levels. &nbsp;This is apparently what Sekulow is trying to claim is broadening the scandal, but Klein asserts there is nothing scandalous in IRS asking questions of these groups, and it isn't a broadening of the scandal at all because there was no wrongdoing at this level of IRS.</p>
<p>The scandal, of course, is that political groups are getting their 501c4 designations approved at all, but the Beltway apparently isn't ready to take this leap.</p>

  </div>
