<p>... as when you find a trout in the milk."</p>
<p>May we not know them by their chosen names and ask the next question? Or is it that we can, but the IRS, in conferring a set of considerable tax advantages, cannot?</p>
<p>For me, Tea Party says ideology, political ideology. And that ideology may well edge into real, honest, straightforward, non-objectionable political activity such as registering voters, holding rallies with candidates as guests or speakers, a website with links to conservative political action groups. It may be that some or all of these are not enough - in kind or degree - to disallow 501c status.</p>
