   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">Nope- it is a scandal</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1212198/50293796#c65?mode=alone;showrate=1#c65">2+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:92953">VClib</a>, <a href="/user/uid:120104">coffeetalk</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>When the IRS acts in a political manner it definitely is a scandal. Which is why the President took swift action on the matter. The initial explanation was it just a few rogue agents in Cincinnati. That obviously is not the case.<br /></p>
<blockquote>it's not a "scandal" if the IRS asks groups applying for special tax status to verify their eligibility.</blockquote>
Is IS a scandal if they target certain groups because of their beliefs.
<blockquote>The problem comes if some groups are treated differently than other groups because of their political belief.</blockquote>
They were. The IRS used inappropriate, political and ideological terms to target conservative applications for 505(s) status.
<p>And exactly who has claimed that groups seeking tax exempt status should not be examined?</p>
<p>I'll stick with the President on this matter, you can try to defend the partisan actions of the IRS. Although I fail to understand why.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:159779">Mister T</a> on <a href="/comments/1212198/50293796#c65">Wed May 29, 2013 at 12:00:57 PM PDT</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
  </div>
</li> 


	





